         <abstract>
            <p>On the basis of a fully discrete trigonometric Galerkin method and two grid iterations we propose solvers for integral and pseudodifferential equations on closed curves which solve the problem with an optimal convergence order |u&lt;sub&gt;N&lt;/sub&gt; - u|&lt;sub&gt;λ&lt;/sub&gt; ≤ c&lt;sub&gt;λ,μ&lt;/sub&gt;N&lt;sup&gt;λ - μ&lt;/sup&gt;|u|&lt;sub&gt;μ&lt;/sub&gt;, λ ≤ μ (Sobolev norms of periodic functions) in O (N log N) arithmetical operations.</p>
          </abstract>
